### Summary

Issue #491 has two concrete, high-impact gaps: (1) the app's root containers use `bg-white dark:bg-gray-900` instead of the dark design-system token `bg-canvas`, making the app appear white in CI and for new users; and (2) screenshot test seed data is too sparse to catch UI regressions.

### Metadata

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Complexity | LOW |
| Files to UPDATE | 3 (`App.tsx`, `useTheme.ts`, `visual.spec.ts`) |
| Files to CREATE | 0 |
| Total Tasks | 4 |

### Key Patterns Discovered

- `App.tsx:115` — `bg-white dark:bg-gray-900` must become `bg-canvas` (design token defined in `index.css:--color-canvas: #0b1326`)
- `useTheme.ts:18` — `return 'system'` fallback is why CI/Playwright sees light mode; change to `return 'dark'`
- `visual.spec.ts:10-86` — mock data shape (all field names) documented; new Things/history/findings must mirror it exactly

### UX Transformation

- **BEFORE**: White app in CI; 3 generic Things, 1 greeting message, 1 finding in tests
- **AFTER**: Always-dark canvas; 7 diverse Things (5 type_hints), 5-turn chat, 4 distinct findings, 2 calendar events; 11 screenshot scenarios

### Risks

- `bg-canvas` Tailwind utility: verify `index.css` `@theme` block before editing App.tsx (mitigation: read file first — P0 mandatory reading)
- Type icons for `project`/`person`: check ThingCard.tsx for rendering — screenshots will still capture titles even without icons

### Confidence Score

**9/10** — All changes are highly localized (2 lines + mock data), no new abstractions, patterns directly mirrored from existing code. The only uncertainty is whether `type_hint: 'project'` renders distinctly in ThingCard (doesn't affect plan correctness).

