---

## Test Coverage Analysis: PR #677

**Verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES**

### Critical Finding (score 9/10)

**Missing snapshots for `full layout – all data populated` test.**

The new test at `visual.spec.ts:466` saves to `full-layout-all-populated.png`, which Playwright resolves to:
- `full-layout-all-populated-chromium-linux.png`
- `full-layout-all-populated-dark-chromium-linux.png`

Neither file exists in the repo. CI will fail on both the `chromium` and `dark-chromium` projects with "snapshot doesn't exist" errors. The `sidebar-diverse-things` pair was correctly committed; this pair was not.

**Fix**: `npm --prefix frontend run test:screenshots:update`, visually inspect, commit the two PNGs.

---

### Medium Finding (score 4/10)

**No unit test for `useTheme.ts` default change.**

The `'system'` → `'dark'` fallback has no unit test. Coverage is implicit via visual tests (fresh browser = no localStorage = default applied), but explicit documentation of the contract is missing. Not a blocker — the hook file has no test file at all currently.

---

### Positive

- **Dark coverage is automatic**: `playwright.config.ts` has a `dark-chromium` project that runs all `visual.spec.ts` tests with `colorScheme: 'dark'`, so every test automatically generates a `*-dark-chromium-linux.png` baseline. No per-test `emulateMedia` needed.
- **Mock data enrichment is comprehensive**: 5 `type_hint` values, 4 finding types, 5 messages, calendar events — good visual regression signal.
- `App.tsx` class-token refactor is well-covered by all existing full-layout tests.
