**Summary of findings:**

**HIGH — Missing baseline snapshots (CI-blocking)**
The `'full layout – all data populated'` test (`visual.spec.ts:466`) references `full-layout-all-populated.png` but neither `full-layout-all-populated-chromium-linux.png` nor the `dark-chromium` variant were committed. The `sidebar-diverse-things` test correctly committed both variants — this test was missed. Fix: run `test:screenshots:update`, inspect the 2 new PNGs, and commit them.

**LOW — New tests lack mobile viewport variants**
The two new tests cover desktop + dark-desktop (via the playwright project matrix) but have no mobile viewport variant. CLAUDE.md mandates desktop + mobile + dark-desktop coverage. Existing pattern: `page.setViewportSize({ width: 390, height: 844 })` in the `'briefing panel – populated (mobile)'` test.

**Everything else looks good:** the `bg-canvas` swap is consistent with how all other components already use the token; the `useTheme.ts` default change is a clean single-line fix; the mock data enrichment is well-structured with correct array indexing.
